===Etymology===
English translation of {{etyl|ru|en}} {{m|ru|Санкт-Петербу́рг}}, from {{etyl|de|en}} {{m|de|Sankt}} {{m|de|Peter|Peters}}{{m|de|Burg|burg|Saint Peter's City}}, referring to {{w|Saint Peter}} the [[Apostle]] and alluding to its founder [[tsar|Tsar]] {{w|Peter the Great}}.

